# rest.nvim Examples
# Place cursor on any request and press <leader>rr to execute

### Simple GET request
GET https://api.github.com/users/octocat
Accept: application/json

### GET with query parameters
GET https://httpbin.org/get?name=John&age=30
User-Agent: rest.nvim

### POST request with JSON body
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "active": true
}

### PUT request
PUT https://httpbin.org/put
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 123,
  "status": "updated"
}

### DELETE request
DELETE https://httpbin.org/delete
Authorization: Bearer your-token-here

### Request with headers
GET https://httpbin.org/headers
Accept: application/json
Authorization: Bearer token123
X-Custom-Header: custom-value

### Using variables (define at top of file)
@baseUrl = https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com
@userId = 1

GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}

### POST with form data
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

name=John&email=john@example.com&age=30

### Multiple requests separated by ###
GET https://api.github.com/zen

###

GET https://httpbin.org/uuid

###

# Example: Authentication flow
POST https://api.example.com/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

# Use the token from above response
GET https://api.example.com/protected
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGc...token-from-login
